      "content": "I can help you draft a rejection email that's both professional and kind. Here's a sample:\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the Senior Developer position at [Company Name]. We were impressed by your exceptional technical skills and experience, and I'm grateful for the time you took to interview with us. After careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose skills and fit align more closely with our current needs.\n\nPlease know that this decision is in no way a reflection on your abilities or potential as a developer. You have a strong foundation, and I have no doubt you will find a great opportunity that aligns with your goals.\n\nI want to thank you again for your interest in joining our team and for sharing your expertise with us. We appreciate the time you invested in our process, and I wish you the best of luck in your future endeavors.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\nYou can adjust this template to fit your company's tone and style, but hopefully, it gives you a good starting point.",
